data.title: Toronto Defiant RoKy and Aid Do Yoga: Access Granted
data.description: Malik Forté swings by the Toronto Defiant house to pick up RoKy and Aid for an afternoon of yoga with a special instructor. One of these players is a master of dance and the other is a Ping Pong monster. Find out which is which in this episode of Access Granted presented by Toyota.

data.title: Watchpoint Game Night Part 2
data.description: In the finale of Watchpoint Game night, some of the league’s best players make their attempt to comeback vs the on-air talent.

data.title: Watchpoint Game Night Part 1
data.description: In our first edition of Watchpoint Game night, some of the league’s best players square off versus on-air talent in some of your favorite living room games.

data.title: Game/Set with the Shanghai Dragons’ Dding
data.description: Sneak your way into a massive teamfight with DDing of the Shanghai Dragons, as we take an in-depth look at his settings when playing Sombra. With these tips you’ll be swinging fights with massive EMPs. This is Game/Set brought to you by OMEN by HP.

data.title: Enter the Dragons
data.description: Ushering in the 2-2-2 meta early in Stage 3 and capping it off with a Stage Final win, the Shanghai Dragons are confident that Stage 4 is where the Dragons will breathe the most fire.

data.title: Tactics: How the Shanghai Dragons set up a Pharah Barrage for DDing
data.description: Pharah's Barrage is capable of making explosive plays, but it's a tricky ultimate to use properly. Using Barrage leaves Pharah vulnerable to counterattacks, so she relies a lot on her teammates to land a good one. In this episode of Tactics, we break down a moment from the Shanghai Dragons' Stage 3 Playoffs victory, where every one of the Dragons goes above and beyond to set their Pharah player, DDing, up for a teamfight-winning Barrage. It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: Pressure Rising: Fighting for Playoffs
data.description: As the books begin to close on Stage 4 and the 2019 Overwatch League season, the last remaining eligible teams sound off on their scramble to the playoffs.

data.title: Carpe and Diem: Seize the Friendship
data.description: Having met each other in middle school through gaming, Jaehyeok “Carpe” Lee and Min Sung “Diem” Bae have maintained a friendship from their path to pro and all the way into the Overwatch League. Danny Lim sits down with the two buddies before they face off against each other at the Atlanta Homestand

data.title: Grudge Match: San Francisco Shock vs. Shanghai Dragons
data.description: In a Stage 3 Finals match that went the distance, the San Francisco Shock nearly mounted enough momentum for a reverse sweep before being bested by the damage-heavy Shanghai Dragons. Both teams reflect on that match and make predictions for their Stage 4 rematch.

data.title: Danny Lim’s Backyard BBQ Pool Party
data.description: Danny Lim hosts the 2019 Overwatch League Stage winners in his uncle’s backyard to beat the heat, eat some meat, and talk playoffs.

data.title: Looking Back On an Epic Stage 3
data.description: We take a look back at Stage 3 of the Overwatch League, new faces, great fans, and overall a memorable stage!

data.title: From the Overwatch League Office | Welcome Our Initial Seven Teams
data.description: It’s with great pleasure that we announce the first seven city-based teams entering the Overwatch League.

data.title: Student Becomes The Master – Ryujehong vs Jjonak
data.description: Citing Ryujehong as one of his inspirations for playing competitive Overwatch, the Inaugural Season MVP JJonak discusses New York Excelsior’s upcoming matchup versus the Seoul Dynasty.

data.title: Ryujehong: An Overwatch Dynasty
data.description: Cited as the “O.G.” of Overwatch and as the inspiration for so many pros to pick up the game, Jehong “ryujehong” Ryu reviews his storied career and his legacy as a pro-gamer.

data.title: Fighting for Seoul’s Dynasty
data.description: As the clock ticks down on Stage 4 of the Overwatch League season, the pressure cranks up for the Seoul Dynasty work hard to find that landmark win amid team changes and other struggles.

data.title: Game/Set with the Seoul Dynasty’s ryujehong
data.description: Find out how to keep your team in the fight as ryujehong of the Seoul Dynasty walks you through his settings when playing as Ana. Hear all about who to prioritize with your Nano Boost and how to land those perfect Sleep Darts in this episode of Game/Set brought to you by OMEN by HP.

data.title: Ryujehong: "The strongest team is my team."
Tactics: Seoul Dynasty Clutches a 3v6 with less than 10 Seconds Left
data.description: No matter how one-sided an Overwatch teamfight is looking, it's truly never over until it's actually over. In this episode of Tactics, we review an Overtime teamfight that the Seoul Dynasty miraculously clutched vs. the Chengdu Hunters when they were at a massive numbers disadvantage with only seconds left in their time bank. data.description: With Sigma propelling his way into the 2019 Overwatch League playoffs, Vancouver has seen some significant changes in their play except for big one: winning. Twilight and Tizi discuss the reforms to the Titans lineup and how they aren’t phased when it comes to change.

data.title: Looking to 2020
data.description: Nine players, nine cities, and one goal. We sat down with players from all around the world and discussed how excited they are to be playing in their home cities for the 2020 Overwatch League season.

data.title: Did You Catch That? The Mei Blizzard that ALMOST iced the Shock!
data.description: The 2019 Overwatch League Grand Finals featured some of the most harrowing clutch plays in the game's history. One of these moments featured San Francisco Shock's Rascal scoring a quintuple kill against the Vancouver Titans on the tail end of a teamfight that look doomed for the Shock. In this episode of, "Did You Catch That?", we break down how Rascal may not have been able to pull off this miracle play if the Titans had used their Mei ultimate just a little bit differently.

data.title: Tactics: Bastion ROCKET JUMPS onto a chandelier!
data.description: During the 2019 Grand Finals, the San Francisco Shock's Architect blew the crowd's minds as Bastion when he used his own rockets to blast himself up to a chandelier to win a teamfight vs. the Vancouver Titans. In this episode of Tactics, we examine why and how Architect pulled this move off and how it created an advantage for his team in the ensuing fight.

data.title: Overwatch League on the Red Carpet
data.description: When you work and play in Los Angeles, it’s not hard to find yourself brushing elbows with the stars! Follow the journey of several of our Overwatch League players as they donned their finest threads and strolled the red carpet for Variety’s Power of Young Hollywood party.

data.title: Vancouver’s Favorite 2019 Season Moments
data.description: The dominant Vancouver Titans stroll down memory lane through the 2019 season and remember the best (and worst) plays of the year.

data.title: Eye of the Titans: Vancouver’s Run to the Top

data.description: The Atlanta Reign’s newest star, Andrej “babybay” Francisty, sits down with Malik Forte to discuss his long and winding road to the Overwatch League, battling through adversity, and how a premonition helped lead to the biggest upset in league history.

data.title: Sinatraa: Top of the Charts

As the meta shifted, sinatraa proved he was the real deal by easily transitioning to playing Zarya, quickly becoming one of the best in the League.
